Elon Musk, the founder and CEO of Tesla, bought a 9.2 percent of Twitter share and thus became its biggest shareholder. Previously, Musk had challenged Vladimir Putin one on one on the same platform with Ukraine as the stakes. It would appear that Twitter will be his "secret social media weapon." Editors: Sudeshna Sarkar, Yuan Xin Chief editor: Ge Jing Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)